# Options Roll Protocol

## When to Roll

| Trigger | Action |
|---|---|
| DTE ≤ 7 | DTE roll — same strike, next monthly (~35 DTE) |
| Short option within **2% OTM** | Defensive roll — same or higher strike, next expiry |
| Short option **ITM** | Urgent — execute BTC or roll immediately |
| Premium decayed ≥ 80% | Profit roll — BTC + STO new position same parameters |
| Stop-loss hit (mid ≥ 2× premium collected) | BTC immediately, no roll |

See `options-active-management.mdc` for agent escalation duties.

## Expiry Discovery (CRITICAL)

**Never hardcode an expiry date.** Monthly option expiry varies per symbol.
Always discover dynamically:

```python
from ib_insync import Stock

stk = Stock(sym, 'SMART', 'USD')
ib.qualifyContracts(stk)
chains = ib.reqSecDefOptParams(sym, '', 'STK', stk.conId)
ib.sleep(0.2)

if chains:
    exps = sorted(chains[0].expirations)
    # Get next expiry at least 21 DTE from today
    from datetime import date
    today_str = date.today().strftime('%Y%m%d')
    next_exp = next((e for e in exps if e > today_str), None)
```

Why: Many symbols have non-standard cycles (quarterly, LEAPS only, etc.).
Hardcoded `20260515` type dates will fail with "No security definition" errors
for a large subset of symbols.

## Roll Execution Pattern — Combo Order

Roll = BTC (buy-to-close existing) + STO (sell-to-open next) in a single BAG order
to minimize execution risk and margin impact:

```python
from ib_insync import ComboLeg, Contract, LimitOrder

leg1 = ComboLeg()
leg1.conId    = existing_option.conId   # BTC leg
leg1.ratio    = 1
leg1.action   = 'BUY'
leg1.exchange = 'SMART'

leg2 = ComboLeg()
leg2.conId    = new_option.conId        # STO leg
leg2.ratio    = 1
leg2.action   = 'SELL'
leg2.exchange = 'SMART'

bag = Contract()
bag.symbol    = sym
bag.secType   = 'BAG'
bag.currency  = 'USD'
bag.exchange  = 'SMART'
bag.comboLegs = [leg1, leg2]

# net_credit > 0 means we collect premium on the roll
order = LimitOrder(action='SELL', totalQuantity=qty, lmtPrice=net_credit_per_share)
order.tif     = 'GTC'
order.transmit = True
```

## Pricing a Roll

```python
from ib_insync import Option

# Get mid of existing short
existing = Option(sym, current_expiry, strike, right, 'SMART')
ib.qualifyContracts(existing)
ib.reqMktData(existing, '', False, False)
ib.sleep(1)
tick_existing = ib.ticker(existing)
mid_existing = (tick_existing.bid + tick_existing.ask) / 2  # cost to BTC

# Get mid of new short
new_opt = Option(sym, next_expiry, strike, right, 'SMART')
ib.qualifyContracts(new_opt)
ib.reqMktData(new_opt, '', False, False)
ib.sleep(1)
tick_new = ib.ticker(new_opt)
mid_new = (tick_new.bid + tick_new.ask) / 2  # credit received

net_credit = mid_new - mid_existing   # positive = credit roll
```

Set `lmtPrice` to the net credit rounded to the nearest $0.01.
Use `GTC` so it works overnight if it doesn't fill in the session.

## Strike Selection on Roll

- **DTE roll only:** Keep the same strike.
- **Defensive roll:** Move strike up (calls) or down (puts) by ~5–10% if stock moved.
- **Rescue roll:** Accept a debit roll if necessary to buy time — log reason clearly.

## Logs

Roll execution records go to `trading/logs/` directory.
Use timestamped filenames: `roll_log_YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS.json`.
The `trading/logs/` directory must exist — create with `mkdir -p` if needed.
